CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 4, 1954, pg. 1 reads: "Second Prize Winner - John Ruffing Jr., district sales manager of Carnation Milk Company, is shown presenting a check for $100 to Mrs. Andrew Goodson, 7417 Mount Vernon Street, as he award for her baby daughter's wining of the second prize in Carnation Milk Company's Healthy Baby Contest. Little Andrea Goodson, who weighs 21 3/4 pounds and is 27 inches tall at the age of eight months, smiles good naturedly as the check is awarded. - All Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: John Ruffing Jr. presenting second prize to Andrea Goodson, daughter of Mrs. Andrew Goodson, in Centre Avenue YMCA during Carnation Milk baby contest
